1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,232
A polished AI output is useful because it can accelerate real work.

2
00:00:04,182 --> 00:00:08,596
It is risky when appearance convinces us that judgment is no longer needed.

3
00:00:08,596 --> 00:00:18,259
First, remember the warning in Anthropic's data: artifact conversations showed more direction and iteration, but less visible checking of context, facts, and reasoning.

4
00:00:18,259 --> 00:00:21,576
Second, treat the first output as a starting point.

5
00:00:21,576 --> 00:00:28,913
Use focused follow-ups to expose assumptions, strengthen evidence, compare alternatives, and make uncertainty explicit.

6
00:00:28,913 --> 00:00:32,125
Third, set the collaboration terms in advance.

7
00:00:32,125 --> 00:00:39,365
Ask for challenge, context, grounds, uncertainty, and acceptance criteria instead of confident completion alone.

8
00:00:39,365 --> 00:00:45,144
Finally, run the five-pass checklist: Goal, Gaps, Grounds, Test, and Owner.

9
00:00:45,144 --> 00:00:50,596
If any pass is vague, the work may look finished, but the collaboration turn is not finished yet.

10
00:00:50,596 --> 00:00:52,442
Follow Tiny Agent.

11
00:00:52,442 --> 00:00:55,480
Tiny Agent helps you get better at using AI.
